On Tue, Apr 3, 2018 at 9:27 AM AEST, Matthew Palfrey <matthewpalfrey@gmail.com> wrote:

Hi Heath,

Apologies for the late message, changes below:

1. http://www.strongbybret.com/dashboard.php <http://www.strongbybret.com/dashboard.php>

Week 2

W1
W2
W3
W4

Current round: January/February 2018 (Month 26)
Focus: General Strength

Welcome to Week 2! After a nice deload week you should be ready to increase your effort a bit. Continue to focus on good form and keep a little effort in reserve this week.

Remove the entire section above (in bold).

Replace with:

Week 1: March 19 - 25

Welcome to Week 1 of the new month of workouts! Please remember that your first week should be a deload week in which you don't go for PRs (personal strength records) or go all-out and instead focus on practicing the movements and figuring out what loads to use for the following week. There are no set specifications or percentages for this; just be sure you aren't going to failure or pushing too hard. Now's the time to familiarize yourself with the workouts.

Week 2: March 26 - April 1

Welcome to Week 2! After a nice deload week, you should be ready to increase your effort a bit. Continue to focus on good form and keep a little effort in reserve this week.

Week 3: April 2 - April 8

For week 3, it's time to start ramping up the intensity of your workouts while continuing to be mindful of your form. Bret recommends that you film and review your exercises at least occasionally to ensure that you are performing the lifts properly.

Week 4: April 9 - April 15

This is the last week of this month's workout cycle. Now's the time to increase your effort to near-max levels and try to set some PRs (personal strength records).

2. http://www.strongbybret.com/workouts.php <http://www.strongbybret.com/workouts.php>

Change the grid here to read (left to right, top row to bottom row):

Workout 1 March/April 2018 - links through to a page using this content http://bretcontreras.com/cms/admin.php?menu=workouts&action=edit&num=105 <http://bretcontreras.com/cms/admin.php?menu=workouts&action=edit&num=105>

Workout 1 February/March 2018 - links through to a page using this content http://bretcontreras.com/cms/admin.php?menu=workouts&action=edit&num=102 <http://bretcontreras.com/cms/admin.php?menu=workouts&action=edit&num=102>
Workout 2 February/March 2018 - links through to a page using this content http://bretcontreras.com/cms/admin.php?menu=workouts&action=edit&num=103 <http://bretcontreras.com/cms/admin.php?menu=workouts&action=edit&num=103>

3. Update the main navigation 'Your Program' link list to reflect the 6 current workout pages.

>>> On 28 March 2018 at 17:30, Heath Maguire - Wolf IQ <heath@wolfiq.com.au <mailto:heath@wolfiq.com.au>> wrote:
>>> Hi Matthew,
>>>
>>> It’s strange, it appears the data on the front-end domain strongbybret.com <http://strongbybret.com/> is not linked to the database on the ‘back-end’ domain bretcontreras.com <http://bretcontreras.com/>.
>>>
>>> We are not sure how/why these two have become ‘uncoupled'. So there are 2 options: a bandaid fix, or a more permanent solution.
>>>
>>> Band-aid fix:
>>> We can hard code the changes required, note, this would mean that the back-end CMS would not match what will be on the live front-end.
>>>
>>> Permanent solution:
>>> We can work to get the back-end coupled with the front-end again, restoring the theoretical functionality of the CMS back to normal.
>>>
>>> Time wise the band aid fixes would be relatively quick for simple copy changes etc. The permanent solution would take 4 - 8 hours as we are not 100% across how the CMS has been built, it’s quite propriety and this is our best guess at present.
>>>
>>> Price wise, for these the rate would be $125/hr inc GST.
>>>
>>> Let me know your thoughts and if that helps at all?
>>>
>>> Cheers,
>>>
